<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="476" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[162,778,663,1237]" pageId="31" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis box="[162,263,663,684]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="476">Remarks</emphasis>
: Galatheids, considered as a group to be ubiquitous members of the deep-sea fauna, have been reported from vents and seeps since the discovery of these habitats in the late 1970s (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Chevaldonne P &amp; Olu K" pageId="31" pageNumber="476" pagination="286 - 298" refId="ref63268" refString="Chevaldonne P, Olu K. 1996. Occurrence of anomuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda) in hydrothermal vent and cold-seep communities: a review. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109 (2): 286 - 298." type="journal article" year="1996">Chevaldonné &amp; Olu, 1996</bibRefCitation>
). As pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chevaldonne P &amp; Olu K" pageId="31" pageNumber="476" pagination="286 - 298" refId="ref63268" refString="Chevaldonne P, Olu K. 1996. Occurrence of anomuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda) in hydrothermal vent and cold-seep communities: a review. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109 (2): 286 - 298." type="journal article" year="1996">Chevaldonné &amp; Olu (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, the great morphological similarity among genera and species of galatheids has led to some rather vague general references to these decapods at vents and seeps, such that identification even to genus is not always possible from the literature or from photographs. Although several species have been described and are to date known only from vent areas, all species are assumed by us to be vagrants rather than endemics. See 
<bibRefCitation author="Chevaldonne P &amp; Olu K" box="[250,604,1062,1084]" pageId="31" pageNumber="476" pagination="286 - 298" refId="ref63268" refString="Chevaldonne P, Olu K. 1996. Occurrence of anomuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda) in hydrothermal vent and cold-seep communities: a review. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109 (2): 286 - 298." type="journal article" year="1996">Chevaldonné &amp; Olu (1996: 293)</bibRefCitation>
for an in-depth discussion of sightings of various galatheids (some of which might be chirostylids) that are as yet unidentified. These reports include 
<bibRefCitation author="Kim DS &amp; Ohta S" box="[474,692,1154,1176]" pageId="31" pageNumber="476" pagination="221 - 233" refId="ref69194" refString="Kim DS, Ohta S. 1991. Submersible observations and comparison of the biological communities of the two hydrothermal vents on the Iheya Ridge of the Mid-Okinawa Trough. JMSTCTR Deep-Sea Research 7: 221 - 233 [in Japanese with English summary]." type="journal article" year="1991">Kim &amp; Ohta (1991</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 10, ‘galatheid crabs with broad rostrum’) and other unconfirmed sightings.
</paragraph>
